snippet.textDisplay: Quite the uplifting video. My whole life has only seen increased globalization. The next 40 looks to be marked by deglobalization. In the classic Ricardian model of trade creating wealth, do we have an example of what happens in the collapse of worldwide trade?

snippet.textDisplay: I think it will be less deglobalization and more regional political unions/economic alliances. Less worry about some a-hole promising to liberalize and actually don't.
